description:
Optionally use fsnotify instead of polling for faster response:

```go
func (e *Engine) watchTicksDirectory() <-chan struct{} {
    changes := make(chan struct{}, 1)

    watcher, err := fsnotify.NewWatcher()
    if err != nil {
        // Fall back to polling
        return nil
    }

    watcher.Add(".tick/issues")

    go func() {
        for {
            select {
            case event := <-watcher.Events:
                if event.Op&(fsnotify.Write|fsnotify.Create) != 0 {
                    // Debounce - wait for writes to settle
                    select {
                    case changes <- struct{}{}:
                    default:
                    }
                }
            case <-watcher.Errors:
                // Log and continue
            }
        }
    }()

    return changes
}
```

This is an optimization - polling works but file watching is more responsive.

Acceptance criteria:
- [ ] File watcher detects tick changes
- [ ] Falls back to polling if fsnotify unavailable
- [ ] Debounces rapid file changes
- [ ] Cleans up watcher on shutdown
